OL,3,CThe post-Christmas failures begin, but
OL,4,CNext defies the retail gloom
OL,6,FModella blames an "extremely
OL,7,Fchallenging" trading environment, "an
OL,8,Falarming drop-off in pre-Christmas
OL,9,Ffootfall," and what it calls "highly
OL,10,Fadverse government fiscal policies" -
OL,11,Fin plain English: the chancellor's
OL,12,Frecent Budget decisions.
OL,14,FIt's true that higher taxes and an
OL,15,Fincrease in the minimum wage have put
OL,16,Fextra costs on businesses, while
OL,17,Fconsumer confidence has been weak as
OL,18,Fhouseholds grapple with rising prices
OL,19,Fand unemployment edges up. But not all
OL,20,Fretailers have struggled.
